name=Player Model Reload Utility
id=PlayerModelReloadUtil
description=Forces the engine to rebuild your character's 3D model on demand - via a rebindable keybind (default INSERT) or right-click in-game > Utilities > Reload Player Model. Recovers from the B42 invisible-character bug - where an animation/ragdoll transition (e.g. tripping while mantling a railing) makes model assembly resolve a null mesh ("ProcessedAiScene > No such mesh null") and the character renders as nothing - without having to reload the save. Calls resetModelNextFrame(), the same model rebuild vanilla uses for blood/dirt. Standalone, no dependencies, load order irrelevant. Safe to remove.
modversion=1.0.0
